- **Validation**: Use `@Valid` to enable validation on request parameters and objects in Spring Boot.
- **ControllerAdvice**: Implement global exception handling using `@ControllerAdvice`. Example:
  ```java
  @ControllerAdvice
  public class GlobalExceptionHandler {
      @ExceptionHandler(CityNotFoundException.class)
      public ResponseEntity<String> handleCityNotFoundException(CityNotFoundException ex) {
          return new ResponseEntity<>(ex.getMessage(), HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND);
      }
  }
  ```
- **Actuator**: Use Actuator to monitor and manage your application. Example:
  ```bash
  curl http://localhost:8080/actuator/health
  ```
- **Async**: Enable asynchronous method execution with `@Async`. Example:
  ```java
  @Service
  public class AsyncService {
      @Async
      public void asyncMethod() {
          // Asynchronous code here
      }
  }
  ```
- **Scheduled**: Schedule tasks using `@Scheduled`. Example:
  ```java
  @Component
  public class ScheduledTasks {
      @Scheduled(fixedRate = 5000)
      public void reportCurrentTime() {
          System.out.println("The time is now " + new Date());
      }
  }
  ```
